'''''Creature Venture''''' is a 1980 video game published by [[Highlands Computer Services]].<ref name="Schuette1984">{{cite book |last=Schuette |first=Kim |year=1984 |title=The Book of Adventure Games |url=https://archive.org/details/the-book-of-adventure-games |publisher=Arrays, Inc. |pages=38–41 |isbn=0-912003-08-1}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Creature Venture'' is a game in which the player must find the treasure of the haunted Stashbuck mansion.<ref name="CGW3"/> ''Creature Venture'' was one of the first games to use animation in adventuring.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/Softline_1982_11/page/n23/mode/2up|title = Softline 1982 11}}</ref>

==Reception==
William Zurfluh reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "It will provide many hours of challenging entertainment for even the seasoned expert. In conclusion I would recommend ''Creature Venture'' for either the novice or expert. I do not think you will be disappointed."<ref name="CGW3">{{cite magazine |last=Zurfluh |first=William |title=Micro - Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=March–April 1982 |volume=1 |issue=3 |pages=36}}</ref>

